article_title: $20K OK’d for alternative to Medicaid expansion
article_text:
Cheyenne, WY (82001)

Today

A mix of clouds and sun early, then becoming cloudy later in the day. A stray shower or thunderstorm is possible. High 59F. Winds NNE at 10 to 20 mph..

Tonight

Partly cloudy skies. A stray shower or thunderstorm is possible. Low around 40F. Winds NW at 5 to 10 mph.

article_metadata.news_keywords: , legislature 2016, senate appropriations committee, sen. charles scott, senate file 86, sen. bruce burns, sen. john hastert, medicaid, medicaid expansion
article_metadata.author: James Chilton, Wyoming Tribune Eagle

og.description: CHEYENNE – The Senate Appropriations Committee on Tuesday signed off on a $20,000 appropriation for a bill that would seek an alternative to Medicaid expansion in Wyoming.
